  "description": "Pierre-Joseph Proudhon (1809–1865) was a French political theorist, the first person to call himself an anarchist, and the author of the foundational anarchist claim that 'property is theft' — that private ownership of productive resources is not a natural right but an appropriation enforced against everyone else.",
